         <abstract>
            <p>A short Gǝʿǝz theological treatise which is
              a translation from Arabic. In the early Church this kind
              of text was recited for the baptized faithful after the catechumens had been dismissed.
               Whilst <persName ref="PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus Christ</persName>, as the central celebrated ﬁgure,
               was described and praised without his name being mentioned directly,
               the initiated in the mysteries of the Christian faith knew who was intended.</p>
               <p>Not to be confused with the text also known as <ref type="work" corresp="LIT3978Elmastoagya"/>.
               For texts in the versions than cannot be immediately identified, see
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT6688TeachingMysteries"/>.
               </p>
               <p>Not to be confused with the text also known as <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2444Temher"/>.
               For the texts in the version than cannot be immediately identified, see
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT6688TeachingMysteries"/>.</p>
         </abstract>
